cs.AI, cs.LO, cs.MA, cs.PL, cs.SE 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - This paper proposes a new approach to KR that can be applied to many interesting agents, which is a common topic in AI research. 
2. cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) - The paper discusses the traditional logic of facts and proposes a new approach based on Computability Logic, which falls under the scope of cs.LO. 
3. cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems) - The notion of task logical KR can be applied to represent the tasks accomplished by multiple agents in a system, making it relevant to cs.MA. 
4. cs.PL (Programming Languages) - The paper proposes a new approach to KR, which can be seen as a programming language for representing tasks accomplished by an agent. 
5. cs.SE (Software Engineering) - The paper proposes a new approach to KR that can be used to build sophisticated KRs, which is relevant to software engineering for building intelligent systems.
